dk.statsbiblioteket.util.qa
Annotation Type QAInfo

@Documented
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface QAInfo

Annotation containing all information relevant to extracting QA reports.

author

public abstract java.lang.String author

A free form string naming the author. For clarity use the same author format as in reviewers().

It is suggested to use the Author keyword for CVS controlled code.

This annotation should name the primary responsibly party for this piece of code. In most cases it will be the original author of the document, but if the file receives heavy editing by other parties, they may end up being more appropriate for the listed author.

Returns:
Default:
""

revision

public abstract java.lang.String revision
The current revision of the annotated element. Mostly for use on classes. It is suggested to use the CVS Id keyword for CVS controlled repositories.

Default:
""

deadline

public abstract java.lang.String deadline
Free form string describing the deadline.

Returns:
Default:
""

reviewers

public abstract java.lang.String[] reviewers

Developers responsible for reviewing this class or method.

Fx {"mke", "te"} - use same convention as author().

It is advised to keep a list of all reviewers here, with the last one in the list being the last person to review the code. This way it will be easy to construct a simple audit trail for the code.

Default:
{}

comment

public abstract java.lang.String comment
A freeform comment that can be included in QA reports.

Returns:
Default:
""

Returns:
Default:
dk.statsbiblioteket.util.qa.QAInfo.Level.UNDEFINED

state

The QAInfo.State of the annotated element.

Returns:
Default:
